---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SaaSLayout from '../components/SaaSLayout';
import PasswordManagerApp from '../components/PasswordManagerApp';
---

<Layout 
	title="Free Password Manager • Zero-Knowledge Encryption Vault"
	description="Secura is the best free password manager app offering zero-knowledge password management, dynamic generation, and local-first AES-256-GCM vault security."
	keywords="free password manager, password management, google password manager, password manager, password manager google, best free password managers, password manager recommendations, manage passwords, best password manager, password managers, save password manager, keeper password manager, password manager app"
	ogTitle="Secura Free Password Manager • Premium Zero-Knowledge Vault"
	ogDescription="Secure your digital identity with the best free password manager. Client-side PBKDF2 and AES-256 GCM encryption guarantees your vault remains yours alone."
	ogType="website"
>
	<SaaSLayout activeModule="Password Manager" client:load>
		<PasswordManagerApp client:load />

		<!-- Elegant SEO informational & FAQ section -->
		<div class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-[#070b13] border-t border-slate-200/40 dark:border-slate-800/60 py-16 px-6 sm:px-8 lg:px-12 transition-all">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
				<!-- SEO Article Section -->
				<section class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none mb-16">
					<h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-6 tracking-tight">
						Secura Free Password Manager: Your Ultimate Solution for Client-Side Zero-Knowledge Encryption
					</h2>
					<p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed text-sm mb-4">
						In the modern digital landscape, security is no longer an optional luxury—it is an absolute necessity. With cyber threats, phishing schemes, and database breaches occurring daily, relying on weak, memorable passwords is one of the most significant digital risks you can take. Fortunately, utilizing a powerful, secure, and <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">free password manager</strong> can help you secure your personal data, accounts, and financial information with ease. Our next-generation <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">password manager app</strong> offers state-of-the-art <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">password management</strong> designed to protect your sensitive credentials locally on your machine, ensuring complete privacy through strict zero-knowledge protocols.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mt-8 mb-4">
						Why Dedicated Password Management is Essential
					</h3>
					<p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed text-sm mb-4">
						Many internet users rely on simple web browsers to <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">manage passwords</strong> or use built-in tools like the <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">google password manager</strong> (also commonly searched as <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">password manager google</strong>). While browser autocompletion tools are convenient, they often lack specialized security parameters and advanced organizational features provided by dedicated <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">password managers</strong>. Dedicated client-side software allows you to securely organize, search, audit, and encrypt usernames and security tokens without storing raw, readable text in a third-party server. By switching to a dedicated <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">free password manager</strong>, you secure your data against localized system compromises and unauthorized cloud access.
					</p>
					<p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed text-sm mb-4">
						Industry security researchers consistently provide specific <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">password manager recommendations</strong> indicating that standalone zero-knowledge applications are vastly superior to general browser autofill systems. Standalone vault clients ensure that any credentials you save are protected under a separate master key known only to you. This is where Secura sets a new benchmark for <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">best free password managers</strong>, giving you absolute control over your visual Krypton Vault.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mt-8 mb-4">
						Secura vs. Competitors: How We Stand Out
					</h3>
					<p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed text-sm mb-4">
						When searching for the <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">best password manager</strong>, you will find several options such as the <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">keeper password manager</strong> or other commercial SaaS suites. However, many of these alternatives restrict core features—like the number of active items or device synchronization—behind expensive monthly subscriptions. Secura eliminates these barriers. We believe that top-tier digital safety should be accessible to everyone, which is why we offer a fully featured, robust, and completely <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">free password manager</strong>.
					</p>
					<p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed text-sm mb-4">
						Our <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">password manager app</strong> uses advanced AES-GCM (Advanced Encryption Standard in Galois/Counter Mode) with 256-bit key sizes. Unlike legacy systems, we derive encryption keys right in your browser using secure PBKDF2 cryptography. When you <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">save password manager</strong> records in Secura, they are immediately encrypted before leaving your browser. Not even our server database engineers can see your usernames, passwords, or category names—offering an unprecedented level of absolute zero-knowledge protection.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mt-8 mb-4">
						Core Security Features to Manage Passwords Effortlessly
					</h3>
					<p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed text-sm mb-4">
						Secura provides a rich suite of security and configuration features tailored for both power users and casual internet browsers:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 text-sm mb-4">
						<li><strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">Zero-Knowledge Architecture:</strong> No passwords, master keys, or unencrypted text are ever uploaded, processed, or cached on our backend servers.</li>
						<li><strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">Cryptographically Secure Generator:</strong> Generate highly complex, customizable passwords containing variable weights of uppercase letters, numbers, and custom symbols to eliminate pattern predictability.</li>
						<li><strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">Smart Tagging and Categorization:</strong> Organize your vault items into visual categories like Banking, Social Media, Work, and Personal to streamline daily workflows.</li>
						<li><strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">Local and Cloud Encryption Synchronization:</strong> Enjoy real-time, encrypted backups powered by Google Firebase, giving you cross-device access while keeping all payload strings fully ciphered.</li>
						<li><strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-250">Real-time Domain and Phishing Alerts:</strong> Identify if a domain name matches your stored credentials before autofilling, neutralizing active spoofing attempts.</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<!-- FAQ Accordion Section -->
				<section class="border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 pt-16">
					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-2 tracking-tight">
						Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)
					</h3>
					<p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm mb-8">
						Everything you need to know about secure password management, Google browser integration, and standard recovery procedures.
					</p>

					<div class="space-y-4">
						<details class="group bg-white dark:bg-[#0b0f19] border border-slate-200/60 dark:border-slate-800/60 rounded-xl p-5 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-indigo-500/30">
							<summary class="flex justify-between items-center font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 text-sm cursor-pointer select-none list-none">
								<span>Can I see all my passwords?</span>
								<span class="text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200">
									<svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
								</span>
							</summary>
							<p class="mt-3 text-xs sm:text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
								Yes, in the Secura <strong class="font-medium text-slate-750 dark:text-slate-300">free password manager</strong>, you can easily view and manage all your stored credentials. Once you enter your master password, your vault is decrypted locally on your device, allowing you to search, copy, edit, and view every username, password, and secure note in cleartext.
							</p>
						</details>

						<details class="group bg-white dark:bg-[#0b0f19] border border-slate-200/60 dark:border-slate-800/60 rounded-xl p-5 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-indigo-500/30">
							<summary class="flex justify-between items-center font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 text-sm cursor-pointer select-none list-none">
								<span>Where is your password manager?</span>
								<span class="text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200">
									<svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
								</span>
							</summary>
							<p class="mt-3 text-xs sm:text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
								Secura is a full-stack, cloud-hosted security platform. You can access your zero-knowledge <strong class="font-medium text-slate-750 dark:text-slate-300">password manager app</strong> vault on any desktop or mobile browser. Simply sign in with your email or Google account and decrypt your vault using your secure local master password.
							</p>
						</details>

						<details class="group bg-white dark:bg-[#0b0f19] border border-slate-200/60 dark:border-slate-800/60 rounded-xl p-5 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-indigo-500/30">
							<summary class="flex justify-between items-center font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 text-sm cursor-pointer select-none list-none">
								<span>How to manage our password?</span>
								<span class="text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200">
									<svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
								</span>
							</summary>
							<p class="mt-3 text-xs sm:text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
								To perform effective <strong class="font-medium text-slate-750 dark:text-slate-300">password management</strong>, use a secure vault client like Secura. Create unique, random passwords containing numbers, symbols, uppercase, and lowercase characters for each of your online accounts. Avoid reusing passwords. Secure them in an encrypted vault rather than writing them down, and use a strong master password that only you know to protect the vault.
							</p>
						</details>

						<details class="group bg-white dark:bg-[#0b0f19] border border-slate-200/60 dark:border-slate-800/60 rounded-xl p-5 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-indigo-500/30">
							<summary class="flex justify-between items-center font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 text-sm cursor-pointer select-none list-none">
								<span>How to manage password?</span>
								<span class="text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200">
									<svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
								</span>
							</summary>
							<p class="mt-3 text-xs sm:text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
								To <strong class="font-medium text-slate-750 dark:text-slate-300">manage passwords</strong> safely, sign up for our zero-knowledge free password manager. Avoid saving them directly to unprotected browser extensions. Use our built-in password generator to replace simple, repeating phrases with complex, randomly compiled hash strings.
							</p>
						</details>

						<details class="group bg-white dark:bg-[#0b0f19] border border-slate-200/60 dark:border-slate-800/60 rounded-xl p-5 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-indigo-500/30">
							<summary class="flex justify-between items-center font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 text-sm cursor-pointer select-none list-none">
								<span>How can I see my Gmail password?</span>
								<span class="text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200">
									<svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
								</span>
							</summary>
							<p class="mt-3 text-xs sm:text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
								To view a saved Gmail password, open your chosen password manager tool. If you use Google's built-in services, go to Google Chrome Settings > Autofill and Passwords > <strong class="font-medium text-slate-750 dark:text-slate-300">Google Password Manager</strong> (or search <strong class="font-medium text-slate-750 dark:text-slate-300">password manager google</strong>), find your Gmail credentials, and perform system verification to view. If saved securely in Secura, search "Gmail" in your vault dashboard, unlock the item, and click the eye icon.
							</p>
						</details>

						<details class="group bg-white dark:bg-[#0b0f19] border border-slate-200/60 dark:border-slate-800/60 rounded-xl p-5 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-indigo-500/30">
							<summary class="flex justify-between items-center font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 text-sm cursor-pointer select-none list-none">
								<span>How can I open a password manager?</span>
								<span class="text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200">
									<svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
								</span>
							</summary>
							<p class="mt-3 text-xs sm:text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
								To open the Secura <strong class="font-medium text-slate-750 dark:text-slate-300">free password manager</strong>, simply visit our dedicated Web Vault page. You can also open default browsers security portals by typing <code class="font-mono text-xs text-indigo-500">chrome://settings/passwords</code> in your address bar to launch Google's password utility.
							</p>
						</details>

						<details class="group bg-white dark:bg-[#0b0f19] border border-slate-200/60 dark:border-slate-800/60 rounded-xl p-5 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-indigo-500/30">
							<summary class="flex justify-between items-center font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 text-sm cursor-pointer select-none list-none">
								<span>How do I find my password if I forgot it?</span>
								<span class="text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200">
									<svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
								</span>
							</summary>
							<p class="mt-3 text-xs sm:text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
								If you forgot an individual service's password, use their "Forgot Password" link on the login page to verify your identity via email or SMS. If you forget your Secura master password, we cannot recover or reset it for you due to our zero-knowledge policy. You must use the master recovery key generated during your vault creation to access your account.
							</p>
						</details>

						<details class="group bg-white dark:bg-[#0b0f19] border border-slate-200/60 dark:border-slate-800/60 rounded-xl p-5 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-indigo-500/30">
							<summary class="flex justify-between items-center font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 text-sm cursor-pointer select-none list-none">
								<span>How do I see my email password on my phone?</span>
								<span class="text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200">
									<svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
								</span>
							</summary>
							<p class="mt-3 text-xs sm:text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
								On an iPhone, navigate to Settings > Passwords to view credentials synced with iCloud. On an Android phone, open the Chrome app, tap the three dots, select Settings, and open Password Manager. If you are using our zero-knowledge web application on mobile, simply open Secura, sign in, and search for your email host.
							</p>
						</details>

						<details class="group bg-white dark:bg-[#0b0f19] border border-slate-200/60 dark:border-slate-800/60 rounded-xl p-5 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-indigo-500/30">
							<summary class="flex justify-between items-center font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 text-sm cursor-pointer select-none list-none">
								<span>How do I know my password?</span>
								<span class="text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200">
									<svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
								</span>
							</summary>
							<p class="mt-3 text-xs sm:text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
								If you cannot recall a password and have not saved it to a dedicated vault, check your browser's auto-fill vault (like <strong class="font-medium text-slate-750 dark:text-slate-300">google password manager</strong>). To avoid losing track of keys in the future, save all new credentials immediately to a <strong class="font-medium text-slate-750 dark:text-slate-300">free password manager</strong> vault.
							</p>
						</details>
					</div>
				</section>
			</div>
		</div>
	</SaaSLayout>

